x4freetext: -TOTAL CROSS-SECTION OF WATER AT ROOM TEMPERATURE AND
200 DEG C.-
.DEMOCRITUS RESEARCH REACTOR,
FAST CHOPPER IN THE ENERGY RANGE 0.01 TO 10
EV,
MAN CRYSTAL SPECTROMETER FOR 2ND SERIES OF
MEASUREMENT IN THE ENERGY RANGE 0.03 TO 1.0 EV.
REACTOR.
.THE EQUILIBRIUM PRESSURE OF THE TWO-PHASE
VAPOR LIQUID SYSTEM OF WATER AT 200 DEG C IS 16 AT.
.THE THICKNESS OF THE WATER SAMPLE, WAS 7.3
MM., WITH AN ERROR OF ABOUT 0.02 MM.
CHOPPER FLIGHT PATH = 2257 CM, THE WIDTH OF
THE NEUTRON PULSE = 94 MICRO-SEC, AND WITH A CHANNEL
WIDTH OF 64 MICRO-SEC A RESOLUTION = 5.0 MICRO-SEC/M.
.A BANK OF FOUR BF3 COUNTERS (FAST CHOPPER),
.ZN CRYSTAL AS A MONOCHROMATOR WAS USED. (MAN CRYSTAL
SPECTROMETER)  VARYING THE ANGLE OF THE MONOCHROMATOR
IN STEPS, SEVERAL POINTS BETWEEN 0.03 EV AND 1.0 EV
WERE TAKEN.
COMMENTS ADAPTED.
.THE CROSS-SECTION OF WATER VARIES SLOWLY, NO
RESOLUTION CORRECTION WAS FOUND NECESSARRY.  BUT THE
DATA TAKEN FROM THE FAST CHOPPER WAS CORRECTED FOR
DEAD TIME EFFECT (ABOUT 3 PERCENT IN THE CROSS-
SECTION) AND FOR SINGLE SCATTERING.
.STATISTICAL STANDARD DEVIATIONS.  THEY WERE BETWEEN
ABOUT 0.4 PERCENT IN THE THERMAL REGION AND 1 PERCENT
AT ENERGIES HIGHER OR LOWER THAN THERMAL.  OTHER
SOURCES OF ERROR WERE FOUND TO BE SMALLER THAN THE
STATISTICAL ERROR.
.TOTAL CROSS SECTION AT ROOM TEMPERATURE AND 200 DEG C,
.THE CROSS SECTION PER HYDROGEN ATOM IN WATER, AT ROOM
TEMPERATURE HAS BEEN CALCULATED.  THE OXIGEN CROSS-
SECTION WAS TAKEN AS 3.7 BARNS.
.ABSOLUTE, TRANSMISSION EXPERIMENT.
NEUTRONS.
.TAKEN FROM EANDC(OR)-63.
COMMENT ADAPTED.
